The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Man found hanging
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Man found hanging
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	The body of a youth was found hanging from a branch of a tree at Kushberia, under Uluberia police station, on Friday morning. The mans limbs were tied with ropes and his shirt was torn. The injuries suggested that he had been tortured, said police.         
	nHusband torture: An Alipore court on Friday directed officers of Jadavpur police station to probe an allegation by a BSF jawan, Abdul Kader, that his wife Jaheeda Nasreen had been torturing him. According to the jawan, Jaheeda had been beating him up for eight years. She allegedly hit him with a grinding stone and stabbed his hands with a knife on January 27.        
	nFatal mishap: A 24-year-old conductor in a private bus was killed on Friday afternoon after he fell off the footboard on APC Road. The driver was arrested.        
	nMan murdered: Bechu Saha, a 45-year-old resident of Kashipur, under Calcutta Leather Complex police station, was found dead in a ditch in the area on Friday morning. His body bore multiple injuries. He was murdered while returning home on Thursday night, said police.                                                                                                                                                          
